<item>
            <title>[LU-11575] make debs fail on debian without systemd enabled</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11575</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As not all debian series support systemd, for example Ubuntu 14.04.x, make debs failed with following error, because it always tries to install systemd stuff.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dh_install -p lustre-client-utils&lt;br/&gt;
dh_install: lustre-client-utils missing files (debian/tmp/lib/systemd/system/*), aborting&lt;br/&gt;
make&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: *** &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;binary-lustre-client-utils&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Error 2&lt;br/&gt;
make&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: Leaving directory `/root/lustre&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
dpkg-buildpackage: error: debian/rules binary gave error exit status 2&lt;br/&gt;
make: *** &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;debs&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Error 2&lt;/p&gt;</description>
